      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "```python\ndef sort_orders(orders):\n    return sorted(orders, key=lambda x: (x[0], -x[1], x[2]))\n```\nThis function sorts the orders based on the provided test cases by prioritizing the first element ascending, the second element descending (by negating it), and finally the third element ascending. This structure ensures the required ordering for the given assertions to pass immediately in your pipeline.",
